  "fullArabic": "وَإِذَا طَلَّقۡتُمُ ٱلنِّسَآءَ فَبَلَغۡنَ أَجَلَهُنَّ فَلَا تَعۡضُلُوهُنَّ أَن يَنكِحۡنَ أَزۡوَٰجَهُنَّ إِذَا تَرَٰضَوۡاْ بَيۡنَهُم بِٱلۡمَعۡرُوفِۗ ذَٰلِكَ يُوعَظُ بِهِۦ مَن كَانَ مِنكُمۡ يُؤۡمِنُ بِٱللَّهِ وَٱلۡيَوۡمِ ٱلۡأٓخِرِۗ ذَٰلِكُمۡ أَزۡكَىٰ لَكُمۡ وَأَطۡهَرُۚ وَٱللَّهُ يَعۡلَمُ وَأَنتُمۡ لَا تَعۡلَمُونَ",
  "fullTranslation": "And when you divorce women and they have fulfilled their term, do not prevent them from remarrying their [former] husbands if they agree among themselves on an acceptable basis. That is instructed to whoever of you believes in Allah and the Last Day. That is better for you and purer, and Allah knows and you know not.",
  "fullTransliteration": "wa-idha tallaqtumu al-nisaa fabalaghna ajalahunna fala ta'duluhunna an yankih'na azwajahunna idha taradaw baynahum bil-ma'rufi dhalika yu'azu bihi man kana minkum yu'minu bil-lahi wal-yawmi al-akhiri dhalikum azka lakum wa-atharu wal-lahu ya'lamu wa-antum la ta'lamuna"
